  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cash multisectorielle pour les urgence en Nord Kivu: B&#xE9;ni - Oicha - Eringeti</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The &#x2018;Alternative Responses for Communities in Crisis (ARCC) III&#x2019; project, implemented in North Kivu, with co-financing from UNICEF and the Swiss Agency for Development and Cooperation, has the aim of supporting conflict-affected households to improve their well-being, while building their resilience to future shocks, through multi-sectorial cash assistance. In-line with emergency response programs such as RRMP and based on coordination with the COPIL, the ARCC-III program responds to multi-sectorial gaps in assistance to vulnerable and displaced populations, identified through humanitarian coordination in North Kivu. 
Past experience in implementing this program has shown that unconditional multi-purpose cash transfer programming is a rapid, effective and efficient way of addressing the diversity of needs and levels of vulnerability within communities in crises and addresses inclusion of the most vulnerable groups. Through multi-purpose cash assistance, marginalized groups, minorities, and persons with specific needs are better able to enjoy their rights and access basic goods and services with cash, which is more flexible than in-kind assistance. Beyond responding to immediate needs, cash-based assistance serves to strengthen beneficiaries&#x2019; capacity to manage shocks and stresses in the long-term,  by improving access to financial capital and the improving their resilience to plan for future shocks.</narrative>
  </description>
